  }, "Selecting Indicators:")), mdx("p", null, "Some constructs are difficult to measure. This could be a communication or discomfort thing, a disinformation thing, etc. We an use proxy indicators that capture observable traits without having to ask respondents awkward questions. Proxy indicators should be correlated with the construct. Proxies should dynamically update as indicators - correlation matches as things change."), mdx("p", null, "We must keep in mind that proxies may not be linearly correlated to the construct we're interested in."), mdx("p", null, "An exclusive indicator is one that is correlated with a construct of interest and no others.\nWe can have one indicator or a number of indicators to capture differences. The middle ground is an index, or component, which takes multiple predetermined sample items and weigh their ratios of consumption."), mdx("p", null, "When compiling indices, we want to use methods such as principle components analysis iss to remove correlation between components so their contribution isn't overcounted in the construct of concern."), mdx("p", null, "The z-score index doesn't assume anything about weights of each indicator. ", "[study this]", "."), mdx("hr", null));
